STEP1.2: convert .ped file to .bed file
./plink --file GitRepos/BcSolGWAS/data/genome/chr16_analysis/myCHR16_A --make-bed --out GitRepos/BcSolGWAS/data/genome/chr16_analysis/myCHR16_A
produces .bed, .bim, and .fam
done

STEP1.3: check / make .fam file
fine, except: phenotype is ~empty value (last column, all 1s)
now: input real phenotype
see: 14_C_FAM_importphenos.R
final: plink/.fam
done

STEP2.0: generate haplotypes from sliding window and calculate haplotype-specific association tests
plink --bfile mydata --hap-window 3 --hap-assoc
./plink --bfile GitRepos/BcSolGWAS/data/genome/chr16_analysis/plink/myCHR16_A --hap-window 3 --hap-assoc
ERROR: plink 1.9 recommends BEAGLE
USE PLINK 1.07
plink-1.07-x86_64/plink --noweb --bfile GitRepos/BcSolGWAS/data/genome/chr16_analysis/plink/myCHR16_A --hap-window 3 --hap-assoc --out GitRepos/BcSolGWAS/data/genome/chr16_analysis/haps/chr16_A 
output is plink.assoc.hap

